# Python virtual environment

All Python work for this repo uses the **shared venv** under `breast-cancer-sim/`.

## Location

```
breast-cancer-sim/.venv/     # Python 3.11 — gitignored, create locally
breast-cancer-sim/requirements.txt
```

## Agent commands

Do **not** use bare `python3`, `pip3`, or `python -m pip` — system Python may differ (e.g. 3.9 user site-packages vs project 3.11).

Prefer explicit venv paths from repo root:

```bash
breast-cancer-sim/.venv/bin/python ...
breast-cancer-sim/.venv/bin/pip install -r breast-cancer-sim/requirements.txt
```

Or activate first, then run commands:

```bash
cd breast-cancer-sim && source .venv/bin/activate
python -m pytest simulation-vinesh-philip-chandan/philip-chandan/tests/
```

## Create or refresh

If `.venv` is missing:

```bash
cd breast-cancer-sim
python3.11 -m venv .venv   # or: python -m venv .venv
source .venv/bin/activate
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

## Installing packages

When adding a dependency:

1. Install into the venv: `breast-cancer-sim/.venv/bin/pip install <package>`
2. Add the package to `breast-cancer-sim/requirements.txt` (match existing unpinned style unless pinning is required)
3. Verify: `breast-cancer-sim/.venv/bin/python -c "import <package>"`

## Verify before assuming failure

If `import` fails after `pip install`, check that install targeted `.venv` (wrong interpreter is the usual cause).
